  "translations": {
    "en": "Then Gabriel (peace be upon him) descended upon Ya'qub (peace be upon him) and said: O Ya'qub, shall I not teach you a supplication by which Allah will restore your sight and return your two sons to you? He said: Yes. He said: Say what your father Adam said, so that Allah forgave him; and what Nuh said, so that the Ark settled on Judi and he was saved from drowning; and what your father Ibrahim, the Friend of the Merciful, said when he was cast into the Fire, so Allah made it cool and peaceful for him. Ya'qub (peace be upon him) said: And what is that, O Gabriel? He said: Say: O Lord, I ask You by the right of Muhammad, Ali, Fatima, al-Hasan, and al-Husayn, that You bring me Yusuf and Binyamin together, and that You restore my sight. Ya'qub (peace be upon him) had not finished this supplication before the bearer of glad tidings came, and he cast the shirt of Yusuf upon him, and his sight was restored. He said to them: Did I not tell you that I know from Allah what you do not know?",
